entry.title: Special Weather Statement issued March 6 at 9:55AM CST by NWS La Crosse WI
entry.summary:
The combination of low relative humidity values, breezy winds, and dry grass and brush will result in favorable conditions for fires to spread this afternoon.
Afternoon relative humidity values will fall into the 20 to 25 percent range with winds of 10 to 15 mph, gusting to 20 mph.
Under these conditions, fires will start and spread more easily. Please exercise caution with any activities that involve outdoor fires or create sparks, including campfires, grilling, and operating large equipment. Cigarettes should be disposed of and extinguished properly. Please heed any local burn bans.
